  "response": "If you're considering a septoplasty at Fortis Healthcare, here's some useful information to help you get started:\n\n### What is Septoplasty?\nSeptoplasty is a surgical procedure to correct a deviated septum, which is when the thin wall (nasal septum) between your nasal passages is displaced to one side. This can cause breathing difficulties, frequent nosebleeds, sinus infections, or other nasal obstructions.\n\n### Why Choose Fortis Healthcare?\nFortis Healthcare is a leading healthcare provider in India, known for its state-of-the-art facilities, experienced ENT surgeons, and patient-centric care. Here are some reasons why you might consider Fortis for septoplasty:\n1. **Experienced ENT Specialists**: Fortis has a team of skilled and highly qualified ENT surgeons who specialize in nasal and sinus surgeries.\n2. **Advanced Technology**: Fortis hospitals are equipped with cutting-edge technology for accurate diagnosis and minimally invasive procedures.\n3. **Comprehensive Care**: From pre-operative consultations to post-operative follow-ups, Fortis provides personalized care to ensure a smooth recovery.\n4. **Affordable Packages**: Fortis offers competitive pricing and transparent cost structures for septoplasty and other procedures.\n\n### How to Get Started?\n1. **Consultation**: Book an appointment with an ENT specialist at Fortis to discuss your symptoms and determine if septoplasty is the right option for you.\n2. **Diagnosis**: The doctor may recommend diagnostic tests, such as a nasal endoscopy or CT scan, to assess the severity of the deviation.\n3. **Procedure**: If surgery is recommended, the doctor will explain the process, risks, and recovery timeline. Septoplasty is typically performed under local or general anesthesia and takes about 1\u20132 hours.\n4. **Recovery**: Most patients can go home the same day or the next day. Full recovery usually takes a few weeks, with minimal discomfort.\n\n### Cost of Septoplasty at Fortis:\nThe cost of septoplasty at Fortis can vary depending on factors like the hospital location, surgeon\u2019s expertise, and additional treatments required. On average, the cost ranges between **\u20b950,000 to \u20b91,50,000** in India. It\u2019s advisable to confirm the exact cost during your consultation.\n\n### Tips for Patients:\n- **Choose the Right Surgeon**: Look for ENT specialists with experience in septoplasty and a good track record.\n- **Ask Questions**: Don\u2019t hesitate to clarify any doubts about the procedure, risks, or recovery.\n- **Follow Pre- and Post-Operative Instructions**: Adhere to the doctor\u2019s guidelines for the best outcomes.\n\n### Book an Appointment:\nYou can book a consultation online through the Fortis website or by calling their helpline. Provide your medical history and details to ensure a tailored treatment plan.\n\nFor more specific details, feel free to contact Fortis Healthcare directly or visit their official website. Let me know if you need help with anything else!",
